      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_shtcx_1acbfb668d7b4cfa39aa1a5a5dac3c0e7e" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_shtcx" kindref="compound">Shtcx</ref> task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>Initially the I2C bus will be initialized by calling init function provided by <ref refid="class_i2c_bus" kindref="compound">I2cBus</ref> instance. Then the sensor device will be initialized by call of member function initDevice. For testing purposes a cyclic timer can be activated by commenting in the start method of the timer to initiate a cyclic sampling of the sensor data. <linebreak/>
 Afterwards the function enters the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eTimerExpired: On sample timer expiry sensor data will be sampled by calling function sample and the temperature and humidity data will be read out from internal driver buffer by calling the functions readTemperature and readHumidity. The pointer pElem will be set to 0, to prevent releasing the message because it is allocated static.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eShtcxReport: On report request sensor data will be sampled by calling function sample and the temperature and humidity data will be read out from internal driver buffer by calling the functions readTemperature and readHumidity. Afterwards the data will be send to data manager task by calling the functions reportTemperature and reportHumidity. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
