    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_shtcx" kindref="compound">Shtcx</ref> temperature sensor class derived from task base class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The <ref refid="class_shtcx" kindref="compound">Shtcx</ref> class handle the reception of the temperature and humidity data and report these values to the data manager class on request to add them to the metrics JSON string. Temperature and humidity data is sampled by request. For testing purposes a cyclic timer handling is implemented, but the timer is not started. It can be activated manually in the init function to initiate a cyclic sampling of the sensor data. <linebreak/>
 The <ref refid="class_shtcx" kindref="compound">Shtcx</ref> class provides methods to read temperature and humidity data from the sensor, to initialize the sensor and to report the data to the data manager task. It uses the public zephyr API for the sensor driver provided in file sensor.h. See details in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/sensor_8h.html">Zephyr API documentation</ulink>. <bold>Message Interaction:</bold><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Receive<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Timer interrupt callback</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Shctx task (self)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Power manager task</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Transmit<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Data manager task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Shctx task (self, transmission in timer callback) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
